<paragraph blockId="23.[113,1090,871,1351]" box="[113,766,871,895]" pageId="23" pageNumber="320">
Five 
<typeStatus box="[167,260,871,895]" pageId="23" pageNumber="320">syntypes</typeStatus>
are deposited in NMPC (ex coll. V. Balthasar):
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="320" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="23.[113,1090,871,1351]" pageId="23" pageNumber="320">
<typeStatus box="[113,192,909,928]" pageId="23" pageNumber="320">SYNTYPES</typeStatus>
(5 unsexed specimens): ‘Giufu-Shan / Szechuan / Em. Reitter [p] // Typus [hw, red label] // Det. Dr. Balthasar [p] / 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Balthasar" authorityYear="1932" box="[271,358,935,955]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Drepanocerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arrowi">D. Arrowi</taxonomicName>
m. [hw]’.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[113,1090,871,1351]" pageId="23" pageNumber="320">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[113,289,975,999]" pageId="23" pageNumber="320">Current status.</emphasis>
Junior subjective synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Boucomont, 1912)" baseAuthorityName="Boucomont" baseAuthorityYear="1912" box="[630,1041,975,999]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Sinodrepanus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rex">
<emphasis box="[630,818,976,999]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="320">Sinodrepanus rex</emphasis>
(Boucomont, 1912)
</taxonomicName>
, see 
<bibRefCitation author="JANSSENS A." box="[113,287,1007,1031]" pageId="23" pageNumber="320" pagination="3 - 118" refId="ref24162" refString="JANSSENS A. 1953: Oniticellini (Coleoptera Lamellicornia). Exploration du Parc National de l'Upemba, Mission G. F. de Witte 11: 3 - 118." type="journal article" year="1953">JANSSENS (1953)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="SIMONIS A." box="[298,457,1007,1031]" pageId="23" pageNumber="320" pagination="93 - 104" refId="ref25220" refString="SIMONIS A. 1985: Un nuovo genere e tre nuove specie di Drepanocerina (Coleoptera, Scarabaeidae: Oniticellini). Revue Suisse de Zoologie 92: 93 - 104." type="journal article" year="1985">SIMONIS (1985)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="BEZDEK A. &amp; KRELL F. - T." box="[509,769,1007,1031]" pageId="23" pageNumber="320" pagination="156 - 158" refId="ref23759" refString="BEZDEK A. &amp; KRELL F. - T. 2006: Oniticellini. Pp. 156 - 158. In: LOBL I. &amp; SMETANA A. (eds.): Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera. Volume 3. Scarabaeoidea - Scirtoidea - Dascilloidea - Buprestoidea - Byrrhoidea. Apollo Books, Stenstrup, 690 pp." type="book chapter" year="2006">
<subScript attach="right" box="[509,587,1007,1030]" fontSize="7" pageId="23" pageNumber="320">BEZDĚK</subScript>
&amp; KRELL (2006)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="320" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="23.[113,1090,871,1351]" pageId="23" pageNumber="320">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[113,214,1039,1063]" pageId="23" pageNumber="320">Remark.</emphasis>
The above mentioned synonymy was first proposed by 
<bibRefCitation author="JANSSENS A." box="[806,977,1039,1063]" pageId="23" pageNumber="320" pagination="3 - 118" refId="ref24162" refString="JANSSENS A. 1953: Oniticellini (Coleoptera Lamellicornia). Exploration du Parc National de l'Upemba, Mission G. F. de Witte 11: 3 - 118." type="journal article" year="1953">JANSSENS (1953)</bibRefCitation>
as a result of revisionary study of the 
<typeStatus box="[415,508,1071,1095]" pageId="23" pageNumber="320">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authority="Boucomont, 1912" authorityName="Boucomont" authorityYear="1912" box="[549,946,1071,1095]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Drepanocerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rex">
<emphasis box="[549,743,1072,1095]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="320">Drepanocerus rex</emphasis>
Boucomont, 1912
</taxonomicName>
and a single 
<typeStatus box="[113,196,1103,1127]" pageId="23" pageNumber="320">syntype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Balthasar" authorityYear="1932" box="[231,336,1104,1127]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Drepanocerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arrowi">
<emphasis box="[231,336,1104,1127]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="320">D. arrowi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, both deposited in Muséum national d’Histoire naturele, Paris, 
<collectingCountry box="[1009,1085,1103,1126]" name="France" pageId="23" pageNumber="320">France</collectingCountry>
. Based on Balthasar’s description, 
<bibRefCitation author="SIMONIS A." box="[477,636,1135,1159]" pageId="23" pageNumber="320" pagination="93 - 104" refId="ref25220" refString="SIMONIS A. 1985: Un nuovo genere e tre nuove specie di Drepanocerina (Coleoptera, Scarabaeidae: Oniticellini). Revue Suisse de Zoologie 92: 93 - 104." type="journal article" year="1985">SIMONIS (1985)</bibRefCitation>
however indicated, that the 
<typeStatus box="[938,1021,1135,1159]" pageId="23" pageNumber="320">syntype</typeStatus>
series of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Balthasar" authorityYear="1932" box="[144,250,1168,1191]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Drepanocerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arrowi">
<emphasis box="[144,250,1168,1191]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="320">D. arrowi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(now in NMPC) could be a mixture of two different species, both belonging to his new genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Simonis, 1985" authorityName="Simonis" authorityYear="1985" box="[302,614,1199,1223]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Sinodrepanus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[302,448,1200,1223]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="320">Sinodrepanus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="SIMONIS A." box="[455,614,1199,1223]" pageId="23" pageNumber="320" pagination="93 - 104" refId="ref25220" refString="SIMONIS A. 1985: Un nuovo genere e tre nuove specie di Drepanocerina (Coleoptera, Scarabaeidae: Oniticellini). Revue Suisse de Zoologie 92: 93 - 104." type="journal article" year="1985">Simonis, 1985</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Unfortunately, he was not able to study the complete 
<typeStatus box="[218,301,1231,1255]" pageId="23" pageNumber="320">syntype</typeStatus>
series of this species, nor did he designate a 
<typeStatus box="[785,886,1231,1255]" pageId="23" pageNumber="320">lectotype</typeStatus>
. The current status of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Balthasar" authorityYear="1932" box="[142,240,1264,1287]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Drepanocerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arrowi">
<emphasis box="[142,240,1264,1287]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="320">S. arrowi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is thus not fully resolved, 
<bibRefCitation author="BEZDEK A. &amp; KRELL F. - T." box="[523,778,1263,1287]" pageId="23" pageNumber="320" pagination="156 - 158" refId="ref23759" refString="BEZDEK A. &amp; KRELL F. - T. 2006: Oniticellini. Pp. 156 - 158. In: LOBL I. &amp; SMETANA A. (eds.): Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera. Volume 3. Scarabaeoidea - Scirtoidea - Dascilloidea - Buprestoidea - Byrrhoidea. Apollo Books, Stenstrup, 690 pp." type="book chapter" year="2006">
<subScript attach="right" box="[523,601,1263,1286]" fontSize="7" pageId="23" pageNumber="320">BEZDĚK</subScript>
&amp; KRELL (2006)
</bibRefCitation>
provisionally accepted JANS- SENS’ s (1953) conclusions. The complete 
<typeStatus box="[550,633,1295,1319]" pageId="23" pageNumber="320">syntype</typeStatus>
series of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Balthasar" authorityYear="1932" box="[734,832,1296,1319]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Drepanocerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arrowi">
<emphasis box="[734,832,1296,1319]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="320">S. arrowi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is currently under study by E. Barbero and his coworkers (E. BARBERO, pers comm. 2011).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
